Physical-to-Layer-2 Visibility Mapping
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Map relationships between physical network infrastructure and Layer 2 communications
Deploy hybrid network environments using Vagrant virtualization
Capture and analyze Layer 2 traffic using packet analysis tools
Develop Python scripts to automate network visibility reporting
Generate comprehensive network topology and security assessment reports
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of OSI model (Layer 1 and Layer 2)
Familiarity with MAC addresses, switches, and network segments
Basic Linux command-line skills
Elementary Python programming knowledge
Lab Environment
Your pre-configured cloud machine includes:

Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
Vagrant and VirtualBox
Wireshark/tshark for packet analysis
Python 3.10+ with networking libraries
All required network utilities
